	     Harare - Zimbabwe's influential war veterans on Tuesday called for immediate protests against President Robert Mugabe as parliament moved to impeach the veteran leader. "All the people must leave what they are doing, come to Harare... we just want to see the back of Mugabe immediately. The protests must begin now, we cannot have another hour of Mugabe," said Zimbabwe War Veterans Association chairperson Chris Mutsvangwa. 24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.  